1/ I N S T A L L A T I O N
   -----------------------

- For a complete installation of GATE, user needs to read the Installation Guide
                                                              ------------------

- The installation of this GATE_v6.1.0 version is supported, tested
  and recommanded with the following system set-up and software package :



                        *ooooOOOO0000OOOOoooo*
                        *    S Y S T E M     *
                        *ooooOOOO0000OOOOoooo*

    - Linux : RED HAT & Fedora & Mandrake & Mandriva & Ubuntu...
    - Compiler gcc 4.4 & gcc 4.2 & 4.1 & 4.0 & gcc 3.4 & gcc 3.3 & gcc 3.2


   *oooooooooooooooooOOOOOOOOOOO0000000000OOOOOOOOOOOooooooooooooooooo*
   *    S E T  U P  &  S O F T W A R E  C O N F I G U R A T I O N     *
   *oooooooooooooooooOOOOOOOOOOO0000000000OOOOOOOOOOOooooooooooooooooo*



### Geant4 9.3

    - CLHEP 2.0.4.5
    - ROOT 5.xx (from 20 to last version)
    - lmf_v3.0
    - G4VERSION 9.3

### Geant4 9.4

    - CLHEP 2.1.0.1
    - ROOT 5.xx (from 20 to last version)
    - lmf_v3.0
    - G4VERSION 9.4


NOTES:
-----

* These softwares are validated for 64 bits architectures
** For GATE V6.1 : Use of a different Geant4 versions (than 9.3 or 9.4) may cause incorrect simulation results

2/ C O M P I L A T I O N
   ---------------------

- Configure & Source the "env_gate.sh" file
- Launch "make" or "gmake"


3/ C O M P I L A T I O N   W A R N I N G S
   ---------------------------------------

There may be compilation warnings on some platforms.
